      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VELOCITY MOONLIT (6) flew the lids with a strong early split and led throughout to score an impressive win by 2 lengths over 407m at this track (23.73). Has good speed so she should be prominent despite the draw. The one to beat again. JALAPENO POPPER (7) had been racing in honest fashion recording two placings in a row before finishing fourth (30.19) at this track latest. Has a good record here including three wins. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. LISSY'S GEM (8) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (24.34) last time in a Grade 3/4 at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Can do much better this time. ZABDON IS BACK (2) profiles nicely here at this trip.",
